<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If something is said often enough, even though untrue, people will eventually 
begin to embrace it as truth. That is what is happening with the subject of our 
nation's health care.In spite of what we keep hearing from the White House, we 
do not have a health care crisis. There is no need for a drastic change in our 
system. Our country enjoys the most sophisticated and comprehensive health care 
in the world, and we need to look closely at any new system that might threaten 
to erode it. 
</P>
<P>
 There are some alarming aspects to President Clinton's health care proposal 
that cause me great concern. While there is always room for improvement in any 
program, the drastic changes called for in the Clinton plan are just too risky. 
</P>
<P>
 D. R. O'NEIL 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
