<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / DAILY REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dana Altman, who coached Kansas State to the semifinals of the National 
Invitation Tournament, was hired Thursday as coach at Creighton. 
</P>
<P>
 He replaces Rick Johnson, who resigned March 2 after a 7-22 season and a 
three-year record of 24-59. 
</P>
<P>
 Altman was 68-54 in his four seasons at Kansas State. In 1993, he was the Big 
Eight coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The guessing game over President Clinton and the Final Four is over. He's 
going. 
</P>
<P>
 Clinton had been saying all week he would like to attend the Arkansas-Arizona 
semifinal, but there were lingering doubts about whether he would attend. 
</P>
<P>
 Those doubts ended Thursday when aides said he would fly straight from his 
vacation in Southern California to North Carolina on Saturday. 
</P>
