<TEXT>
<P>
 Starting in November, women's basketball will join the men with a preseason 
NIT. 
</P>
<P>
 A field of 16 was announced Thursday for the first preseason Women's National 
Invitation Tournament.  
</P>
<P>
 Texas Tech, the 1993 national champion, heads the inaugural field. Tech will 
play host to Toledo on Nov. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 The other first-round games, also Nov. 15, are Notre Dame at Northern 
Illinois, Florida International at Vanderbilt, Oklahoma at Montana, Seton Hall 
at Rutgers, Northwestern at Washington, Virginia Tech at Maryland and Marquette 
at Southwest Missouri. 
