<HEADLINE>
<P>
ASK ANITA WINS FEATURE, TURKANA IS DISQUALIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ask Anita was awarded first place in Thursday's $59,475 Avigaition Handicap 
after 2-5 favorite Miss Turkana was disqualified for interference in the final 
strides at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Ask Anita finished three-quarters of a length behind Miss Turkana.Tricky 
Princess finished third, but was moved into second. 
</P>
<P>
 Miss Turkana was dropped to third after the stewards ruled she came over on 
Tricky Princess in the deep stretch, costing Tricky Princess second place. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Chris McCarron, Ask Anita covered 1 1/8 miles on the turf in 1:48. 
She carried 115 pounds and paid $15.40 and $4.60. 
</P>
<P>
 French-bred Tricky Princess returned $3.80. There was no show betting. 
</P>
<P>
 Miss Turkana, ridden by Antonio Castanon, led throughout and appeared on her 
way to her 10th victory in 30 starts until the interference. 
</P>
<P>
 Frenchman's Cove finished last in the race, which was reduced to four starters 
with the late scratch of Viviana. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory, worth $33,975, increased Ask Anita's career earnings to $207,950. 
</P>
</TEXT>
