<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; FESTIVAL ABANDONS CHILD-CARE TENT 
IDEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hopes of providing child care for visitors to the upcoming Conejo Valley Days 
festival fell through this week after an insured day-care provider could not be 
found, festival officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The child-care idea "never got off the ground," said Steve Rubenstein, 
executive director of the Conejo Valley Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 The idea for a child-care tent initially was proposed after marketing surveys 
showed community interest in giving the festival a family focus, said Jennifer 
Cole Cummings, president of Executive Performance Group, the company hired to 
put on the festival. 
</P>
<P>
 Conejo Valley Days is scheduled to begin April 27 and run through May 1. 
