<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; SAN CLEMENTE KNOCKS OFF CAPISTRANO VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chad Wanders pitched a five-hitter and was helped by five home runs as San 
Clemente upset No. 2 Capistrano Valley, 15-1, in a South Coast League baseball 
game Thursday at San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 Wanders (5-0), a senior who has signed to attend Hawaii next fall, had six 
strikeouts and the run he allowed was unearned. Wanders added four hits, scored 
three runs and drove in a run. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Cook hit his first two home runs of the season, a three-run shot in the 
fourth inning and a two-run homer in the fifth. Mike Wood hit his first home 
run in the second. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Firth and Bryan Fischer also had home runs in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 In another South Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 2, Mission Viejo 1 -- Seth Etherton (4-0) pitched a five-hitter, 
struck out nine and gave up one earned run for Dana Hills (7-6-1, 2-1). Chris 
Toomey hit a home run in the sixth inning to put the Dolphins ahead, 2-0. 
Mission Viejo is 0-4 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 11, Garden Grove 0 -- Jim Livernois (5-2) pitched a three-hitter 
with nine strikeouts for host La Quinta (11-2, 4-0). Sean Carlson had four 
hits, including a double, scored two runs and drove in one and Corey Fox had 
two hits, scored a run, and drove in four for the Aztecs. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago 13, Los Amigos 10 -- Outfielder Mark Mooney started Santiago's 
six-run fourth inning with a double to secure the Cavaliers' victory. Third 
baseman Robert Weimann of Santiago hit his first home run of the season at the 
bottom of third with one on. Anthony Duran was three for three with three runs 
scored and three RBIs for the Cavaliers (3-7, 2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 10, University 2 -- Derek Baker hit a fifth-inning solo home run in the 
fifth inning for visiting Tustin (9-3, 4-0). Matt France went two for three, 
had two RBIs and scored a run for the Tillers. Teammate Rick Gonzalez was two 
for three with one RBI. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 3, Irvine 1 -- Josh Tourtellott, who went the distance, struck out 
13 and Damon Durante went three for three and scored one run for Woodbridge 
(5-6, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Metro League: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Shores 13, Corona Christian 4 (5) -- Roldan Chapple struck out nine 
and gave up one hit to lead Pacific Shores (2-3, 1-3). Shawn Bertram hit a 
three-run home run and Chapple added a home run for Pacific Shores, in a game 
shortened by a lack of pitchers by Corona Christian. 
</P>
