<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP; NO. 1 EL TORO ROLLS PAST DANA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Toro boys' volleyball Coach Mike Jagd couldn't have planned it better. 
</P>
<P>
 In fact, he was at a loss for words after the Chargers, ranked No. 1 in Orange 
County, dismantled third-ranked Dana Hills, 17-15, 15-6, 15-7, in a South Coast 
League match Thursday at Dana Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm stunned," Jagd said. "But if we pass well, we can beat anyone." 
</P>
<P>
 It wasn't an ordinary victory for the Chargers . . . they dominated the match. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were in control the whole match," Dana Hills Coach Oz Simmons said. 
"We'd have a string of errors and then we were playing catch-up all night." 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro's Ryan Mariano, a 6-foot-3 outside hitter, had 19 kills and four 
blocks and Doug Thompson had 12 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensively, the Chargers neutralized Dana Hills' bigger players, holding 6-5 
Jeremy Darner to 10 kills, and 6-8 Bob Hefty and 6-4 Matt Clem to nine each. 
</P>
<P>
 But most importantly, the Chargers passed well and setter Todd Steinert, who 
had 47 assists, piloted an efficient attack. 
</P>
<P>
 "Todd did a spectacular job tonight," Jagd said. "He was our MVP. We had Dana 
Hills scouted well and we knew where they were going to be; Todd got the ball 
to the right people." 
</P>
<P>
 The right person was Mariano in most cases. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills played El Toro tough in the first game, and led, 15-14, after Clem 
blocked a spike attempt by Mariano. 
</P>
<P>
 But Steinert went right back to Mariano, whose spike from the right side gave 
the Chargers the side out. Mariano then drew the Chargers even, 15-15, with a 
block and gave them a 16-15 lead with a spike from the back row. 
</P>
<P>
 Clem missed a spike long on game point and the Dolphins never got any closer. 
</P>
<P>
 In another South Coast League match: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 3, Mater Dei 0 -- Gabe Gardner had 11 kills for the Tritons (6-0, 
2-0), who won 16-14, 15-2, 16-14. Mark Pozsgai had 17 kills for Mater Dei (2-5, 
0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 3, Rancho Alamitos 0 -- Trung Khuu had five aces for La Quinta (6-3, 
5-1), which won 15-12, 15-6, 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 3, Los Amigos 0 -- Greg Blackner had 21 kills and setter Alber 
Cardenas had 35 assists for Garden Grove (3-5, 3-2), which upset Los Amigos 
(4-1 in league), 17-15, 15-7, 15-8. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 3, Santiago 1 -- Ian Cheesman had 20 kills, Josh Pagtalunan had 16 
and Mike Parsons had 15 for Pacifica (2-5, 2-3) in a 15-9, 15-6, 14-16, 15-4 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 3, Irvine 2 -- Junior Nathan Bennett had 30 kills and Steve Jobes 
added 18 for Woodbridge (4-4, 4-2), which won 11-15, 6-15, 15-9, 15-12, 15-12. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 3, Servite 0 -- Nate Martin had 12 kills and eight blocks and Mike 
Carney added nine kills and eight blocks for Ocean View (3-4, 2-3), which won 
15-2, 16-14, 15-9. 
</P>
