<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPEN HOUSE TO HONOR FORMER COACH AMBROSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An open house to honor former Pacifica and Los Amigos high school Coach Wayne 
Ambrose will be from 2 to 4 p.m. April 10 at the New Community Church in 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Ambrose, who has cancer, retired from teaching in 1988. He coached football 
and track and field in the Garden Grove Unified School District for 33 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Friends and former players are invited to attend. Donations to help cover 
Ambrose's medical costs will be accepted that evening or can be sent to: 12791 
Brittany Woods Dr., Santa Ana, Calif. 92705. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information call: (714) 442-9240. 
</P>
</TEXT>
