<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC IRVINE BEATS WISCONSIN IN TENNIS TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine beat Wisconsin, 5-2, in one quarterfinal of the UC Irvine men's 
tennis tournament Thursday at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 UCI's Julian Foxon beat Jordan Richman, 6-2, 6-4, at No. 3 singles to improve 
his winning streak to eight.UC Irvine advanced to play Harvard in one semifinal 
and Alabama Birmingham plays South Alabama in the other. Both matches are at 1 
p.m. in the UC Irvine tennis stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 2, Concordia 2 (14) -- Alex Vicario had an RBI single to score 
pinch-runner Adam Virchis from second with two out for host Concordia 
(12-17-1). Jake Miller allowed eight hits and two runs, one earned, in 13 
innings. He had four strikeouts. Jason Smith had two hits for Chapman (8-16-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Boise State 6, Cal State Fullerton 3 -- Kara Kolb won, 6-4, 6-4, to earn her 
second consecutive victory and freshmen Jennifer Camfield and Mandy Gomez each 
won for Cal State Fullerton (7-13). Boise State is 9-8. 
</P>
