<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; MOORPARK PULLS OUT 7-6 VICTORY IN BOTTOM OF 9TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tom Anderson's sacrifice fly drove in Kent Cote with the winning run in the 
bottom of the the ninth, giving Moorpark College a 7-6 victory over Imperial 
Valley in a Channel Coast tournament consolation bracket game Thursday at 
Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders (11-8) tied the score on Ryan Briggs' squeeze in the eighth.Kevin 
Nykoluk and Alex Alvarenga each had two hits and two runs batted in for the 
Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 12, Oxnard 5 -- Joe Torres and Jim Seguine each had three hits 
and an RBI for Oxnard (10-13) in a loss to Rancho Santiago (22-6) in the 
semifinal of the Channel Coast tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Southwestern 5, Pierce 4 -- Cesar Martinez collected two hits and Keith 
McElwee singled in two runs for the Brahmas (15-11) in the championship game of 
the Grossmont tournament.  
</P>
<P>
 Southwestern (20-4) scored the go-ahead run in the fifth inning on a passed 
ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 14, Canyons 8 -- Chris Pfatenhauer, who hit his first home run of the 
season, and Ari Jacobs had three hits each for the Cougars (9-13), but it was 
not enough in a Hancock tournament consolation game at Santa Maria.  
</P>
<P>
 Canyons, which has lost five in a row, was eliminated. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. City 5, Mission 4 (14 innings) -- Freshman right-hander John Ramiro (1-3) 
took the hard-luck loss for Mission (15-13) despite pitching nine innings of 
two-hit ball while allowing one earned run. Erik Lazarus was three for four 
with two runs and an RBI for Mission. 
</P>
