<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; COMMUNITY 
COLLEGE BOARD OKS PAY HIKES FOR 3 GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three of the largest employee groups in the Los Angeles Community College 
District will get 3% pay raises retroactive to January. 
</P>
<P>
 The district's seven-member board unanimously approved a pair of new 
three-year contracts with its faculty and staff unions and a separate action 
giving the same raise to unrepresented employees. 
</P>
<P>
 The raises approved Wednesday will be the first since the 1989-90 school year 
for permanent faculty, technical and clerical staff, and non-union workers. 
</P>
<P>
 The faculty contract also provides a separate 5.7% raise in the hourly rate 
paid to part-time instructors who won't get the regular 3% raise. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials in the financially strapped district said most of the money for the 
raises will come from $13 million in savings the district expects to achieve 
from health plan changes. 
</P>
