<TEXT>
<P>
 El Segundo police arrested a suspect this week they believe tried to kill a 
witness in the slaying case of an El Segundo City Councilman's daughter. 
</P>
<P>
 Police would not release detailed information about the attack but said the 
witness came to police after the Feb. 9 slaying of Tairree Lynn West, 25, and 
reported hearing plans to rob the woman's apartment, said Police Sgt. Bill 
Fleming. 
</P>
<P>
 The witness was not a member of the West family, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Four suspects in the slaying of West are being held without bail. They have 
been ordered to stand trial and are scheduled to be arraigned today in Torrance 
Superior Court on murder and attempted murder charges. They could face the 
death penalty if convicted in the slashing and strangulation death of West. The 
murder charge carries a special circumstance allegation that the killing was 
done during a burglary. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, Robert Brendon Foster and Linnette O'Neill Blocker, both 18; 
Marcus Terral Brewington, 19, and Erica Dawn Olson, 20, are also charged with 
the attempted murder of the dead woman's 12-year-old daughter, Ashley. The 
child was stabbed in the neck and left for dead, but managed to dial 911. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe robbery was one of the motives in the crime, and that West and 
Foster had been involved in a dispute. 
</P>
