<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE GIRLS FROM ALEMANY RECEIVE ALL-STATE BASKETBALL RECOGNITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Samantha Rigley, Carly Funicello and Kelly McKay, who helped Alemany High 
reach the Southern Section Division II-A girls' championship game, have been 
named to the Cal-Hi Sports all-state basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany is one of the top girls' teams in California, so the talented trio 
could be piling up awards for another year or two. 
</P>
<P>
 Rigley, a 5-foot-10 guard, was named the girls' state junior player of the 
year. McKay, a 5-10 forward, was named to the all-underclass junior team and 
Funicello (6-3) was named to the all-underclass sophomore team. 
</P>
<P>
 Rigley and Funicello also were selected to the All-Division II team, which is 
based on enrollment. Mikko Giordano of Buena, a 6-foot senior forward, was 
named to the All-Division I team. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura's 5-7 junior guard Ember Brown and 6-1 sophomore center Nicole 
Greathouse of Buena also were named to their all-underclass teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Four boys' players from the region were selected to all-underclass teams, led 
by twins Jason (6-8) and Jarron Collins (6-7), a pair of highly regarded 
front-court players from Harvard-Westlake. Guards Brock Jacobsen (6-4) of 
Crescenta Valley and Arthur Lee (6-0) of North Hollywood made the 
all-underclass junior team. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior center Alex Lopez (6-10) of Campbell Hall was named to the All-Division 
V team and Damian Cantrell (6-4) of Santa Clara made All-Division IV. 
</P>
<P>
 Kris Johnson (6-5) of Crenshaw, who played for two seasons at Montclair Prep, 
made the all-state third team. STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</TEXT>
