Yes: 61% No: 26% Don't know: 13% * 
</P>
<P>
 Have the Clintons engaged in wrongdoing in Whitewater? Yes: 27% No: 26% Don't 
know: 47% SOURCE: Los Angeles Times Poll How the Poll Was Conducted 
</P>
<P>
 The Times Poll interviewed 1,608 California adults, including 1,211 registered 
voters, by telephone from March 26 through 29. Telephone numbers were chosen 
from a list of all exchanges in the state. Random-digit dialing techniques were 
used so that listed and non-listed numbers could be contacted. Interviewing was 
conducted in English and Spanish. Results were weighted slightly to conform 
with census figures for sex, race, age and education. The margin of sampling 
error for the total and registered voter samples is plus or minus 3 percentage 
points. For certain other sub-groups the error margin may vary. Poll results 
can also be affected by other factors such as question wording and the order in 
which questions are presented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
