<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES NAMES THEATER CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laurie Winer, a New York theater writer and an associate editor at Harper's 
Bazaar, has been named theater critic for the Los Angeles Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Winer has written theater criticism and features extensively for the New York 
Times and the Washington Post. She also served as Off-Broadway critic for the 
Wall Street Journal and was a theater columnist for New York Woman magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 Winer is a graduate of New York University, where she was a double major in 
film and English. She will join the staff in June, replacing Sylvie Drake, who 
retired. 
</P>
</TEXT>
