<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.N. Security Council unanimously urged North Korea to allow full nuclear 
inspections, adopting a statement that lacks the strong sanctions threat sought 
by Washington.Under a compromise worked out with China, the main opponent to 
such a threat, the council adopted a statement that instead only hints at 
further action if North Korea continues to refuse to cooperate. North Korea 
quickly repudiated the U.N. statement and called for talks on the matter with 
the United States. But the Pyongyang government said that it would not permit 
further inspections. 
