<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; UKRAINE; CHERNOBYL REACTORS UNSAFE, AGENCY SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chernobyl nuclear power plant, site of the world's worst nuclear disaster, 
remains unsafe, the United Nations' nuclear watchdog said.Harsh weather has 
caused serious deterioration, such as gaps in the concrete shell sealing off 
the Chernobyl nuclear reactor that exploded in 1986, the International Atomic 
Energy Agency warned. Inspectors also found "numerous safety deficiencies" in 
the two reactors still operating at the Ukrainian plant. The U.N. agency said 
experts will probably meet in April to discuss solutions. 
