<P>
BLAST IN FRENCH REACTOR KILLS 1; NO LEAKS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An explosion set a closed nuclear reactor on fire in southern France on 
Thursday, killing one man and injuring four people, but officials said no 
radiation contamination was detected. 
</P>
<P>
 The Atomic Energy Commission said the blast knocked down a giant, 
3,200-square-foot slab of concrete, sparking a sodium fire in a tunnel some 
distance from the core of the experimental reactor, which was being dismantled. 
The cause of the blast was unknown. 
</P>
