<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; PEDESTRIAN CROSSING HIGHWAY HIT, KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pedestrian trying to cross South Coast Highway near Victoria Drive was 
struck by a passing vehicle Wednesday night and died en route to a hospital, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Jose Trinidad Verela Aguilar, 30, of Mexico, had darted through 
South Coast Highway's two northbound lanes and was crossing the southbound 
lanes when he was struck by a car about 7:45 p.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A physician who witnessed the accident performed cardiopulmonary resuscitation 
on Aguilar until paramedics arrived. He was then flown to South Coast Medical 
Center, where he was pronounced dead, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the vehicle, a 34-year-old man, was not detained, police Sgt. 
Greg Bartz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Blood samples from both the driver -- who volunteered to take the test -- and 
the victim will determine whether either had been drinking, Bartz said. 
FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</TEXT>
