<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; CITY OKS 2ND-UNIT ADDITIONS TO LOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council this week gave preliminary approval to an ordinance that will 
allow second units to be added to residential lots. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the ordinance, any of the city's 9,054 single-family residences might be 
allowed to add an extra unit to the property. The units must be occupied by 
family of the owner.  
</P>
<P>
 The second units might not be allowed in areas where parking is too limited or 
where lots are too small. 
</P>
<P>
 After city planners come up with recommendations regarding lot size, potential 
traffic problems and possible restrictions, the council will consider taking 
final action on the ordinance, officials said.MIMI KO 
</P>
