<P>
MAN KILLED, 2 HURT IN GANG FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One man was killed and two others were injured Thursday afternoon during a 
fight that involved about a dozen gang members, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ricky Michaels, 18, of Placentia was stabbed several times in the chest during 
the fight, which broke out at 4:45 p.m. in the courtyard of an apartment 
complex in the 3100 block of Pearl Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Michaels was taken to Placentia Linda Community Hospital in Placentia, where 
he died about 45 minutes after the attack, said Sgt. Danny Becerra. 
</P>
<P>
 Injured in the melee were 20-year-old Charles Ernest Matthews of Placentia and 
a 17-year-old boy from Anaheim. Both were stabbed in the torso and are in 
stable condition, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are still trying to piece together what happened," Becerra said. "Nobody 
has been arrested and we are still interviewing witnesses." 
</P>
<P>
 Matthews and the injured teen are admitted gang members, as was Michaels, 
Becerra said. 
</P>
<P>
 The stabbing was Fullerton's second homicide of the year. Becerra said there 
has been a recent increase in gang activity in the area where the stabbing 
occurred. 
</P>
