</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Treasury Sells $16.6 Billion of 1-Year Bills: The bills were sold at an 
average rate of 4.30%, the highest rate in almost two years. The rate was 27 
basis points above last month's average of 4.03% and the highest since 4.34% at 
the April, 1992, auction, the Treasury said.The average price was 95.652, and 
the yield to maturity on the bills was 4.51%. The high price and low yield on 
the bills were 95.672 and 4.28%. The low price and high yield were 95.652 and 
4.30%, and 100% of the high bids were accepted. Tenders totaled 
$44,235,793,000. Treasury accepted $16,602,793,000 of the tenders, including 
non-competitive bids of $717,038,000 from individual investors. The 
bid-coverage ratio, which compares securities awarded to bids received, was 
2.66. 
</P>
