<P>
 Hasbro Named in Antitrust Suit: The complaint, filed in federal court in New 
York by Anti-Monopoly Inc., alleges that Hasbro is using discriminatory and 
predatory pricing policies to drive small board-game manufacturers out of the 
market. The suit also charges that Toys 'R' Us Inc. and Kmart Corp., two of the 
top board-game retailers, are conspiring with Hasbro to maintain Hasbro's 
monopoly in the market. Anti-Monopoly is seeking $15 million in damages, and 
has asked the court to order divestiture of all board-game companies acquired 
by Hasbro in recent years, including Milton Bradley, Parker Brothers and 
Selchow & Righter. 
