<P>
 GM Recalls Natural-Gas-Powered Trucks on Safety Defect: General Motors Corp. 
said it is recalling all 2,500 of its natural gas-powered pickup trucks on the 
road, after two of the vehicles' fuel tanks ruptured and exploded earlier this 
year. GM said owners of the 1992 and 1993 full-size pickups can exchange them 
for comparably equipped 1994 gasoline-powered half-ton or three-quarter-ton GM 
pickups.If the owner chooses not to exchange the natural gas-powered truck, the 
company said, it will purchase the vehicle. Despite the defect, GM said it will 
continue with its program to develop a natural gas vehicle fuel system for both 
cars and trucks. About 90% of the 1992 and 1993 trucks are used by utility 
fleets in California and Texas. 
