<P>
Business; Part D; Page 6; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
130 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times correspondent 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home of the Brave: Beleaguered California homeowners facing a foreclosure may 
want to check out a new book called "How to Fight Foreclosure and Win With 
Honor." 
</P>
<P>
 Jensen Publications in Huntington Beach recently introduced the book, which is 
designed to offer foreclosure solutions to Californians who want to save their 
homes. 
</P>
<P>
 The 450-page book provides homeowners with techniques for how to negotiate a 
better deal with their lender, how to lower interest rates and principal and 
how to sell their homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Jensen, with more than 20 years' experience in real estate, spent four years 
researching the book. He even guarantees that anyone who reads the eight 
options contained in the book and follows the simple action plan will be able 
to find a solution to foreclosure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
