<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: PLAZA HOME MORTGAGE REPORTS $6.6-MILLION PROFIT FOR '93 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Plaza Home Mortgage Corp., the Santa Ana mortgage banking company, reported a 
profit of $6.6 million, or 57 cents a share, for 1993, which included a 
third-quarter after-tax charge of $9.3 million related to the decline in 
interest rates.That compared to a profit of $14.5 million, or $1.31 a share, 
recorded for 1992. Annual revenue rose 63% to $136.8 million from $83.8 
million. For the fourth quarter, profit increased 61% to $5.3 million, or 45 
cents a share, from $3.3 million, or 31 cents a share. Three-month revenue more 
than doubled to $45 million from $21 million. 
