<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASADENA ART ALLIANCE PICKS GRANT WINNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pasadena Art Alliance has awarded $70,525 in grants to seven arts 
organizations to support their 1994 exhibition, scholarship and education 
programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The grantees include Pasadena's Armory Center for the Arts ($20,000), Art 
Center College of Design ($18,000), Pasadena City College ($5,525) and Kidspace 
Museum ($5,000). 
</P>
<P>
 Other grantees are Los Angeles' Museum of Contemporary Art ($15,000), the Otis 
School of Art and Design ($5,000) and the Santa Monica Museum of Art ($2,000). 
</P>
